          <actionDate>2016-04-28</actionDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Zombie Property Relief Act of 2016 </b></p> <p>This bill authorizes the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB) to assess a specified fine against a mortgagee that has failed to maintain residential real property that is subject to a federally-related mortgage in foreclosure (nuisance property) until ownership has been transferred to a new owner and the deed for such property transfer has been recorded.</p> <p>The CFPB shall establish a system for reporting the existence of nuisance properties. </p>]]></text>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2016-06-22T19:30:41Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
        </item>
